127
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,870
When I got there, I found that Joy was closed

128
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:43,780
and the owner was nowhere to be found.

129
00:07:43,780 --> 00:07:44,830
Then, as I turned around,

130
00:07:44,830 --> 00:07:46,490
two hooligans blocked my way,

131
00:07:46,659 --> 00:07:48,060
and we ended up fighting.

132
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:49,840
Did you beat them up?

133
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,040
Did you win the fight?

134
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,270
How is that possible?

135
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:54,440
Then how did you come back to take the exam?

136
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,560
I took the chance and ran away.

137
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,740
I ran really, really fast,

138
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,420
but still missed the English listening section.

139
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:03,550
Who holds a grudge against you anyway?

140
00:08:04,090 --> 00:08:05,750
Should I ask my dad

141
00:08:05,770 --> 00:08:07,650
if he can let you retake the listening test?

142
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:09,230
Will your dad agree?

143
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:10,990
I don't know.

144
00:08:13,050 --> 00:08:15,120
Anyways, I think

145
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:18,390
we should let Big Mouth Xu know about this and have him handle it.

146
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:20,860
The person who did this has really gone too far,

147
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:21,800
don't you think?

148
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:24,130
Yes, yes, let's go find Dean Xu.

149
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:26,010
Sure, let's go together.

150
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:27,120
There's strength in numbers.

151
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:27,850
Let's go.

152
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:29,180
Sit down.

153
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,040
Thank you very much.

154
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:32,830
Thank you for not killing me.

155
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:35,840
What does that mean?

156
00:08:35,909 --> 00:08:37,490
During the last exam,

157
00:08:37,490 --> 00:08:39,289
I got scolded by him for fighting.

158
00:08:39,289 --> 00:08:41,409
This time, when he asks why I was late

159
00:08:41,409 --> 00:08:43,380
and we explain, he'll definitely find out about the fight.

160
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:45,060
I would definitely get scolded by him.

161
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:47,390
That's true. We don't have any evidence.

162
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:49,200
And we can't prove that those two hooligans

163
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,530
got into the school and started the fight.

164
00:08:51,620 --> 00:08:54,580
Alright, then we won't go to my dad for now.

165
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:57,950
This is really strange. I thought about it.

166
00:08:58,470 --> 00:09:00,540
Why would two hooligans from off-campus

167
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,290
be able to get into our school?

168
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,190
Who holds a grudge against you?

169
00:09:10,540 --> 00:09:12,420
There's only one truth. I got it.

170
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:13,980
It must be Zhai Tao.

171
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,650
Oh, Zhai Tao.

172
00:09:16,740 --> 00:09:18,190
Zhai Tao? Who?

173
00:09:18,530 --> 00:09:19,240
Zhai Tao.

174
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:21,370
The trash who kicked Uncle Mute last time.

175
00:09:21,370 --> 00:09:22,120
Oh.

176
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,280
What did those two hooligans look like?

177
00:09:34,930 --> 00:09:36,390
I don't remember clearly.

178
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,790
Anyway,

179
00:09:38,610 --> 00:09:40,950
they were both not very tall, about 1.7 meters.

180
00:09:40,950 --> 00:09:41,860
Black hair.

181
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:44,950
I also forgot what clothes they were wearing.

182
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:46,370
I don't really remember

183
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,700
much else.

184
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:50,140
I'm not criticizing you.

185
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:51,510
You have face blindness

186
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:53,120
and can't remember their names.

187
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:55,460
How do you expect me, a little detective, to figure things out?

188
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:57,490
They were there to beat me up.

189
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:59,430
Should they introduce themselves?

190
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:00,780
I don't know their names.

191
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:02,780
That makes sense. You're so stupid.

192
00:10:03,850 --> 00:10:05,280
Who usually protects you?

193
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,590
Are you feeling strong and confident now?

194
00:10:06,590 --> 00:10:08,430
Who protects me usually?

195
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:09,870
Who?

196
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:11,410
My dad protects me.

197
00:10:11,410 --> 00:10:12,590
Stop picking and eat.

198
00:10:12,590 --> 00:10:13,590
